      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="5202_">
    
         <p>Papers of John Watermelon Redington consist of a typescript, "Scouting in Montana," 16 pages, circa 1870-1879, regarding his adventures fighting American Indians in Montana; correspondence with Owen Wister and others; correspondence between his daughters regarding him and their grandfather, A. B. Meacham; a scrapbook, 1 volume; and Elinor Meacham Redington reminiscences.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
